-- в”Ђв”Ђ Snipcart в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Developer-focused JavaScript shopping cart that adds full e-commerce checkout to any website or static site, owned by Duda since 2021.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$usage-based / transaction fee$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$20 per month minimum, or 2% per transaction on monthly sales above $1,000$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Quebec City, Canada$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Snipcart Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Snipcart lets developers add a shopping cart and checkout to any website with a few lines of code. See pricing (2% per transaction), features, pros and cons.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Snipcart is an e-commerce platform designed for developers who want to add shopping cart and checkout functionality to an existing website, static site, or custom-built application without adopting a full storefront builder. Founded in 2013 and headquartered in Quebec City, Canada, Snipcart was acquired by website-building platform Duda on September 3, 2021, and continues to operate as a developer-oriented e-commerce layer under that ownership. The core product is a JavaScript and HTML snippet that can be dropped into virtually any site, regardless of the underlying framework or content management system, turning any page into a sellable product with cart and checkout capability. It supports physical goods, digital downloads, and subscription or recurring billing, and integrates with multiple payment gateways so merchants can accept cards and other payment methods. Snipcart provides a merchant dashboard for managing orders, inventory, discounts, taxes, and multi-currency sales, along with webhooks and an API for custom integrations into other business systems. Pricing follows a usage-based model: Snipcart charges 2 percent of transaction value plus the underlying payment gateway's own fees, with a flat $20 per month minimum charge applied to accounts whose monthly sales fall under $1,000. There is a free-to-start development and testing mode with no credit card required, so developers can build and test an integration before going live and incurring transaction fees. Snipcart is commonly used by freelance developers and small agencies building custom sites for clients, as well as businesses that want e-commerce bolted onto an existing site rather than migrating to a dedicated platform like Shopify.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '33d8b578-c949-41fd-b5e1-f9c8acf9190a';

