-- в”Ђв”Ђ Snowplow в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Open-source and enterprise behavioral data platform that collects, validates, enriches, and delivers event-level customer data to your own cloud data warehouse in real time.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium / usage-based (quote-based for managed platform)$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2012, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$London, United Kingdom$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Snowplow Review 2026: Open-Source Behavioral Data Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Snowplow collects and delivers first-party behavioral event data straight to your own data warehouse. See features, open-source vs managed BDP pricing, and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Snowplow, operated by Snowplow Analytics Ltd, is a behavioral data platform founded in 2012 and headquartered in London, United Kingdom, with roughly 130 to 160 employees as of 2026. It is distinct from Snowflake, the separate cloud data warehouse company, though the two names are frequently confused; Snowplow is a data collection and pipeline company, not a data warehouse. Snowplow's core purpose is capturing granular, event-level behavioral data, such as web clicks, mobile app interactions, and server-side events, validating and enriching that data in real time, and delivering it directly into a customer's own cloud data warehouse or lake, including Snowflake, BigQuery, Databricks, and Redshift. This first-party-data-ownership model differs from typical black-box analytics tools, since the raw event data lands in infrastructure the customer already controls. Snowplow is available in two forms: an open-source Community Edition, with trackers and enrichment components released under Apache 2.0 and a self-hosted pipeline governed by the Snowplow Limited Use License Agreement (SLULA) 1.1, and Snowplow BDP (Behavioral Data Platform), a fully managed commercial offering with a UI console, enterprise security, and support, priced on a custom quote basis tied to monthly event volume, number of sources and destinations, and support tier. Snowplow offers a 14-day free trial of the managed platform with no credit card or sales call required, and typically provides discounts of 15 to 25 percent for multi-year commitments. The platform is commonly used by data engineering and product analytics teams that need highly customizable, AI-ready behavioral data infrastructure at scale, particularly where strict data ownership or GDPR-style compliance requirements make third-party analytics black boxes unsuitable.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '62cb1717-61b9-4a9b-aab8-e3aeee5ab747';

